  "texts": [
    "Multi-channel attention-based methods, such as MHSAN and MA-RNN [10,11], highlight the correlations and importance between different modalities and their internal discourse through attention mechanisms.",
    "Quantum theory methods, as the latest attempt, like the QMN model, use quantum interference theory to simulate the interactions between different modalities, presenting a unique perspective and potential [12,13].Despite significant progress in the field of multimodal emotion recognition, existing methods still face a series of challenges.",
    "Firstly, methods based on tensor fusion often come with a large number of parameters, which not only increases the computational burden but also leads to a higher risk of model overfitting.",
    "Secondly, a common issue in multimodal emotion analysis research is the overreliance on limited datasets.",
    "Existing datasets usually provide uniform multimodal annotations, but this approach fails to fully capture the independent emotional characteristics of each modality, limiting the accuracy of capturing differences across modalities."
  ],
